cs.GR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper discusses virtual reality systems and their limitations, which falls under the graphics category. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a solution for negating the effects of latency in networked virtual environments, which falls under the networking and internet architecture category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper briefly examines the use of artificial neural networks in extrapolation methods, which falls under the artificial intelligence category. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper discusses a method for improving the performance and usability of virtual reality systems, which falls under the software engineering category. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses a networked client/server environment, which falls under the distributed computing category.
